 Java array is an object which contains an elements of similar data types. 
 Additionally the elements of an array stored in a contiguous memory location.
 It is a data structure where we store similar elements.
 We can only store fixed size of element i java array.

 There are 3 ways to declare an array.
     dataType[] arr;   
     dataType []arr;   
     dataType arr[];  
    
Instantiation of an Array in Java.
     data_type var_name[] = new data_type[];
 